PHYSICAL LAYER ->   physical connection between the ports, whose primary			role is communicating raw bit streams

DATA-LINK LAYER ->  provides high-level functions, such as error corrections			and flow control

NETWORK LAYER ->    provides addressing and routing

TRANSPORT LAYER ->  provides transparent and reliable transfer of data 				between systems

SESSION LAYER ->    responsible for establishing and maintaining connections			between network applications

PRESENTATION LAYER -> responsible for presenting the data to applications in 			a syntax or language they understand. Allows for things			    like encryption and data compression

APPLICATION LAYER -> keeps track of the requirements of the application
